Videos.Title: HipRx 01
Videos.Description: For improving range of motion and increasing weight-bearing: \n\nThe first HipRx workout focuses on improving range of motion and increasing weight-bearing through your joints. If you experience any knee sensitivity consider using a towel for the kneeling positions. If you are currently undergoing physical therapy please consult your doctor to ensure this program aligns with your treatment plan.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: HipRx

Videos.Title: HipRx 02
Videos.Description: For pelvic stability and expanding range of motion:\n\nThe second HipRx workout improves pelvic stability and expands the range of motion exercises. A towel is recommended for those with knee sensitivity during kneeling positions and can also assist with some movements. If you are currently in physical therapy please consult your doctor to ensure this program is suitable for you.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: HipRx

Videos.Title: HipRx 03
Videos.Description: For core strength and stability and greater range of motion:\n\nThe third HipRx workout introduces a standing workout flow incorporating balance exercises that target core strength and stability while continuing to enhance range of motion. A resistance band is not required but can help build additional strength and stability. A chair may be used for extra balance support if needed. If you are currently in physical therapy please consult your doctor to ensure this program is suitable for you.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: HipRx

Videos.Title: HipRx 04
Videos.Description: For range of motion balance stability and strength:\n\nThe fourth HipRx workout delivers a cumulative routine that integrates range of motion balance stability and strength. You can make the workout more challenging with a resistance band and yoga block. For those with knee sensitivity a towel is recommended for kneeling positions and a chair can provide additional balance support if necessary. If you are currently in physical therapy please consult your doctor to ensure this program is suitable for you.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: HipRx

Videos.Title: HipRx 05
Videos.Description: For total body mobility balance stability and strength:\n\nThe fifth HipRx workout integrates key movements into a total body workout designed to enhance range of motion mobility balance stability and strength. A resistance band is optional for added challenge. If you experience knee sensitivity a towel is suggested for kneeling positions and a chair can provide extra balance support if needed. If you are currently in physical therapy please consult your doctor to ensure this program is suitable for you.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: HipRx

Videos.Title: PowerCuffs - Shoulders \u0026 Legs 02
Videos.Description: This advanced PowerCuffs workout utilizes BFR to build strength in your shoulders and lower body. Join DDP and Britt Baker for a dynamic shoulder and leg workout that can be performed with weights resistance bands or dynamic resistance alone. The leg exercises incorporate knees over toes positions helping to strengthen and protect your joints while building muscle safely and effectively. You\u0027ll go through six workout series - three for shoulders and three for legs - designed to develop lasting strength and deliver real results. Once you incorporate this into your PowerCuffs training shoulder and leg day will become your new obsession!\n\nEnsure you understand proper usage sizing and fit before using PowerCuffs to get the most out of Blood Flow Restriction Training (BFRT) and DDPY. Please note that if you are new to weight training you will experience muscle soreness 1-2 days after each workout.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDP LIVE

Videos.Title: PowerCuffs - Biceps \u0026 Triceps 02
Videos.Description:
Release Date: 09.19.24

Join DDP and IFBB Pro Carolyne Marquez for an intermediate bicep and tricep PowerCuffs workout utilizing BFR to cultivate lean muscle and boost strength gains! DDP will lead you through a superset strength training routine designed around the PowerCuffs to promote optimal muscle engagement using light weights and resistance bands safely and effectively. You will be doing 6 series of workouts as supersets allowing one body part to recover as the other is worked. DDP will encourage you to get one more set of 5 reps in on the last set of each series so remember - listen to your body and do what you can do! DDP lists the workouts you'll be doing in the beginning so be sure to check this one out from the start so you can prepare your equipment ahead of time.

Ensure you understand proper usage sizing and fit before using PowerCuffs to get the most out of Blood Flow Restriction Training (BFRT) and DDPY. Please note that if you are new to weight training you will experience muscle soreness 1-2 days after each workout.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDP LIVE

Videos.Title: 100 Squat Challenge
Videos.Description: Release Date: 05.06.25\n\nLooking to take your leg day to the extreme? The 100 Squat Challenge is calling your name! This high intensity lower body blast is designed to push your limits build strength and leave you feeling unstoppable! You\u0027ll knock out 100 squats in dynamic sets that challenge both your muscles and your mindset. But we\u0027re not just crushing legs - we\u0027re training smart. Between squat sets you\u0027ll engage in targeted back and core work that helps relieve pressure on the spine supports proper posture and strengthens your foundation. By building a stronger back and core between sets you\u0027ll not only protect your body - you\u0027ll amplify your power and performance. Ready to rise to the challenge? Let\u0027s get after it - one squat at a time!

Videos.Title: Stand/Sit/Sculpt w Payge
Videos.Description: Release Date: 11.22.22\n\nGet ready to sculpt strengthen and stabilize with Payge in this dynamic low impact workout that uses a chair as your ultimate support tool! This routine focuses on toning your legs glutes quads and core all while improving balance and control. The best part? It\u0027s designed with versatility in mind! If you have knee sensitivities follow Payge\u0027s lead and use the chair for support. If not you can make it more challenging by performing the workout on the mat. This is the perfect intro to Payge\u0027s sculpt workouts - accessible for all levels and guaranteed to leave you feeling strong energized and ready for more!

Videos.Description:
Release Date: 10.19.2021

Videos.Title: PowerCuffs - Beginner Biceps \u0026 Triceps 01
Videos.Description: This beginner PowerCuffs workout utilizes BFR to specifically target and strengthen your bicep and tricep muscles! DDP leads you through a traditional strength training routine designed around the PowerCuffs to build muscle with light weights and resistance bands safely and effectively. You will be doing 4 series of workouts - 2 for biceps 2 for triceps. If this is your first time watch the video through and focus on learning the fundamental movements correctly before performing the series of exercises. This is a great starting point for anyone new to strength training. \n\nEnsure you understand proper usage sizing and fit before using PowerCuffs to get the most out of Blood Flow Restriction Training (BFRT) and DDPY. Please note that if you are new to weight training you will experience muscle soreness 1-2 days after each workout.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDP LIVE

Videos.Title: 100 Squat Challenge
Videos.Description: Release Date: 05.06.25\n\nLooking to take your leg day to the extreme? The 100 Squat Challenge is calling your name! Videos.Title: PowerCuffs - Shoulders \u0026 Legs 02
Videos.Description: This advanced PowerCuffs workout utilizes BFR to build strength in your shoulders and lower body. Join DDP and Britt Baker for a dynamic shoulder and leg workout that can be performed with weights resistance bands or dynamic resistance alone. The leg exercises incorporate knees over toes positions helping to strengthen and protect your joints while building muscle safely and effectively. You\u0027ll go through six workout series - three for shoulders and three for legs - designed to develop lasting strength and deliver real results. Once you incorporate this into your PowerCuffs training shoulder and leg day will become your new obsession!\n\nEnsure you understand proper usage sizing and fit before using PowerCuffs to get the most out of Blood Flow Restriction Training (BFRT) and DDPY. Please note that if you are new to weight training you will experience muscle soreness 1-2 days after each workout.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDP LIVE

Videos.Title: PowerCuffs - Biceps \u0026 Triceps 02
Videos.Description:
Release Date: 09.19.24

Join DDP and IFBB Pro Carolyne Marquez for an intermediate bicep and tricep PowerCuffs workout utilizing BFR to cultivate lean muscle and boost strength gains! DDP will lead you through a superset strength training routine designed around the PowerCuffs to promote optimal muscle engagement using light weights and resistance bands safely and effectively. You will be doing 6 series of workouts as supersets allowing one body part to recover as the other is worked. DDP will encourage you to get one more set of 5 reps in on the last set of each series so remember - listen to your body and do what you can do! DDP lists the workouts you'll be doing in the beginning so be sure to check this one out from the start so you can prepare your equipment ahead of time.

Ensure you understand proper usage sizing and fit before using PowerCuffs to get the most out of Blood Flow Restriction Training (BFRT) and DDPY. Please note that if you are new to weight training you will experience muscle soreness 1-2 days after each workout.

DDP leads you through a traditional strength training routine designed around the PowerCuffs to build muscle with light weights and resistance bands safely and effectively. You will be doing 4 series of workouts - 2 for chest 2 for back. If this is your first time watch the video through and focus on learning the fundamental movements correctly before performing the series of exercises. This is a great starting point for anyone new to strength training. \n\nEnsure you understand proper usage sizing and fit before using PowerCuffs to get the most out of Blood Flow Restriction Training (BFRT) and DDPY. Please note that if you are new to weight training you will experience muscle soreness 1-2 days after each workout.
Videos.Tags.Name: POWERCUFFS

Videos.Title: PowerCuffs - Beginner Shoulders \u0026 Legs 01
Videos.Description: This beginner PowerCuffs workout utilizes BFR to strengthen your shoulders and traps while the squat series works your whole lower body! DDP leads you through a routine designed around the PowerCuffs to build muscle using your own bodyweight light weights and resistance bands safely and effectively. You will be doing 4 series of workouts - 2 for legs 2 for shoulders. Feel free to use your own bodyweight during the squat series like DDP is doing or incorporate weights as Tom and Payge are as you progress and your leg strength improves. If this is your first time watch the video through and focus on learning the fundamental movements correctly before performing the series of exercises. This is a great starting point for anyone new to strength training. \n\nEnsure you understand proper usage sizing and fit before using PowerCuffs to get the most out of Blood Flow Restriction Training (BFRT) and DDPY. Please note that if you are new to weight training you will experience muscle soreness 1-2 days after each workout.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDP LIVE

Videos.Title: PowerCuffs Cooldown
Videos.Description: This official PowerCuffs Cooldown routine is designed to stretch and relax tired muscles promoting overall recovery and flexibility. DDP takes you through a total body stretch with a special focus on your back hips and knees which take a lot of the stress during weightlifting. This restorative routine will help realign the spine hips and knees while also aiding in muscle recovery. Feel free to add this cooldown after your PowerCuffs workouts or once a week as an active recovery day! Remember to remove your PowerCuffs before beginning this routine.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDP LIVE

Videos.Title: Kneehab 01
Videos.Description: Join Matt Kilgore as he guides you through the first workout in our Kneehab series which focuses on improving range of motion while building strength and stability in your knees. This series can be used to supplement your physical therapy program and beyond. It can also be a great preventative for those experiencing knee pain. A towel is suggested to help facilitate some of the movements. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Kneehab

Videos.Title: Kneehab 02
Videos.Description: Matt Kilgore continues working on range of motion in the second workout of our series while adding in some weight-bearing exercises. A soft cushion or pillow is recommended to assist with potential discomfort. Additionally a towel and yoga blocks may be useful in facilitating some of the movements. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Kneehab

Videos.Title: Kneehab 03
Videos.Description: Join Matt Kilgore for our third workout focusing on balance and stabilizing your core helping to prepare you for the strengthening workouts to come. A chair is suggested to help facilitate some of the movements. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Kneehab

Videos.Title: Kneehab 04
Videos.Description: In our fourth video Matt Kilgore combines all of the movements from the previous ones to give you a total body workout incorporating range of motion balance stability and strength. A soft cushion or pillow is suggested to assist with potential discomfort. Additionally a towel and yoga blocks may be useful in facilitating some of the movements. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Kneehab

Videos.Title: Kneehab 05
Videos.Description: Join Matt Kilgore for our final video which is a culmination of all the functional movements you\u0027ve performed throughout the series. This is a total body workout that will work range of motion balance stability and strength. A chair may be useful in facilitating some of the movements. Additionally a soft cushion or pillow is suggested to assist with potential discomfort. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Kneehab

Videos.Title: Shoulder Strong 01
Videos.Description: Join Matt Kilgore as he guides you through the first of our Shoulder Strong series workouts focused on gaining range of motion in your shoulder. This series can be used to supplement your physical therapy program and beyond. It can also be a great preventative for those experiencing shoulder pain. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Shoulder Strong

Videos.Title: Shoulder Strong 02
Videos.Description: Join Matt Kilgore as he leads you through the second workout in our Shoulder Strong series introducing weight-bearing positions to build strength while continuing to work on range of motion. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Shoulder Strong

Videos.Title: Shoulder Strong 03
Videos.Description: In the third video of our series Matt Kilgore introduces additional movements to help you build stability in your shoulder while continuing to work on strength and range of motion. A resistance band is suggested to help build further strength and stability but not required to perform the workout. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Shoulder Strong

Videos.Title: Shoulder Strong 04
Videos.Description: Matt Kilgore brings you a strength based workout in the fourth video in our series which also continues working on stability and range of motion to help improve your shoulder mobility. A resistance band is suggested to help build additional strength and stability but not required to perform the workout. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
Videos.Tags.Name: DDPY PT: Shoulder Strong

Videos.Title: Shoulder Strong 05
Videos.Description: Join Matt Kilgore as he guides you through the final workout of the Shoulder Strong series! This workout is a culmination of all the movements you\u0027ve performed throughout the last four videos to improve the range of motion strength and stability in your shoulders. A resistance band is suggested to help build additional strength and stability but not required to perform the workout. If you are currently doing physical therapy please check with your doctor to make sure this program fits in with your treatment.
